Many argue that we should run authorize in the `Controller`. That&#39;s fine. I would probably end up with some empty controllers classes. Controllers that exist only to extend an authorization controller, which has a callable method I can use to check if the request can proceed.

Adding models to `Controller` through arguments, like the example above, I at least don&#39;t have to create an empty controller for every page. Usually, we should find some controller methods in the class.

